Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.22,0:00:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there was an incoming call to Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s\Ncell phone from the Inubushi home?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.26,0:00:21.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, about two hours before she fell from the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.39,0:00:25.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, those four adopted children seem\Neven more suspicious, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.02,0:00:28.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suddenly asking her to buy something while she was out...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.98,0:00:31.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that the time of her return would be delayed.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.74,0:00:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And we can assume it was possible for the culprit to\Norder the dog attack on her after dark, can't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.95,0:00:39.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shouldn't it be three people?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.74,0:00:42.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miyuki san has an alibi after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.20,0:00:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miyuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is also suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.54,0:00:51.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she had wanted to get the dog to attack, she could've blown a\Ndog whistle without being discovered even while she was with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.88,0:00:54.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus the fact that Miyuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was directly below the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.55,0:01:00.01,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The only person in that house who isn't\Nsuspicious is the bedridden old lady, Satomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.45,0:01:00.01,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inubushi Satomi (74)\NHead of the Inubushi Family
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.49,0:01:01.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.64,0:01:04.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why have you been taking charge this whole time?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.39,0:01:06.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you one of Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s assistants like Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.25,0:01:08.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.90,0:01:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.90,0:01:12.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I said stop with the "assistant" thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.01,0:01:19.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Causing your eyelids to swell and permeating your heart...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.20,0:01:20.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tear drops serve as a prelude to a wealth of drama.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.00,0:01:23.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The burning demon dog's footsteps...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.43,0:01:24.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the mystery of the spheres that were left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.25,0:01:26.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.96,0:01:28.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.83,0:01:30.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.94,0:03:15.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The household under a dog's curse...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.02,0:03:16.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Inubushi family
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.73,0:03:19.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The previous head of the household,\NTsunechika, died five years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.32,0:03:24.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And his surviving widow, Satomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nhad been confined to bed as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.91,0:03:30.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she were to pass away, the enormous Inubushi inheritance\Nwould be divided among the eight adopted children.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.16,0:03:35.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But those adopted children began\Nto die by bizarre means, one by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.84,0:03:41.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We proceeded to investigate the case, but the\Nfourth victim appeared right before our very eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.80,0:03:47.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more, the crime scene was dotted with\Nburning footprints that were left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.14,0:03:52.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that the ablazed demon dog really exists?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.85,0:03:55.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The serial killings of the Inubushi family...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.36,0:03:57.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Has it truly been the work of a devilish, cursed canine?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.90,0:04:05.53,Signs,,0,0,0,,(FOOTSTEPS CHAPTER)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.90,0:04:05.53,Signs,,0,0,0,,INUBUSHI CASTLE\NTHE ABLAZED DEMON DOG
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.87,0:04:09.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.20,0:04:12.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only the demon dog were like this too...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.30,0:04:21.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.18,0:04:25.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.34,0:04:27.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did something light up over there?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.70,0:04:51.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.12,0:04:56.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Get up!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.87,0:04:58.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The entrance is right there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.84,0:05:08.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.05,0:05:09.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All this racket...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.01,0:05:11.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The demon dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.31,0:05:13.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The demon dog showed up in the backyard!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.47,0:05:14.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Demon dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.56,0:05:16.56,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's ridiculous!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.85,0:05:18.65,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inubushi Yoshiya (34)\NAdopted Child of Inubushi
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.56,0:05:18.65,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,There's no way it could appear on the grounds of the house!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.96,0:05:22.30,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inubushi Miyuki (28)\NAdopted Child of Inubushi
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.46,0:05:20.30,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.40,0:05:22.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,It jumped over the fence and got on our property?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.57,0:05:25.15,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inubushi Takako (47)\NAdopted Child of Inubushi
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.71,0:05:24.05,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.11,0:05:25.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,That's just absurd!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.65,0:05:29.99,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Inubushi Tomoaki (42)\NAdopted Child of Inubushi
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.86,0:05:27.45,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,In any case...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.45,0:05:29.99,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Let's not go outside for the time being\Nwith it sounding so dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.62,0:05:34.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hachi is barking...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.08,0:05:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't Hachi in danger?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.33,0:05:39.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We need to bring Hachi inside!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.21,0:05:41.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hold on, you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.76,0:05:49.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's just an ordinary marble no matter how you look at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.93,0:05:53.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A pachinko ball, a ping-pong ball, a pearl bead...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.97,0:05:54.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And a marble?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.31,0:05:58.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just what is the culprit trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.48,0:06:00.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It must mean that, that!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.10,0:06:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What comes to mind if I say "dogs" and "beads"?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.57,0:06:03.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.32,0:06:04.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.44,0:06:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You just thought up another stupid pun, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.61,0:06:10.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever it may be, just tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.74,0:06:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're all ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.03,0:06:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It might even end up being a hint.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.66,0:06:17.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nah...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.87,0:06:19.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's stupid, so never mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.54,0:06:23.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.63,0:06:24.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't start getting all uppity!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.88,0:06:25.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.46,0:06:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Never!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.67,0:06:28.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm not going to say it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.39,0:06:34.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Indeed...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.01,0:06:37.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There seem to be traces of the grass having been burnt.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.68,0:06:40.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The rope that was stretched around the\Nedge of the cliff had been cut, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.31,0:06:41.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.61,0:06:45.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sign was taken down, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.28,0:06:50.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The guidepost at the fork in the road a ways back had also fallen.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.14,0:06:52.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.57,0:06:56.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In this darkness and without the guide\Npost, sign and the protective rope...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.41,0:06:58.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she had been chased by a dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.75,0:07:02.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wouldn't be a surprise that she'd fly off the edge of the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.21,0:07:08.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only problem is the identity of the fiery demon\Ndog that is said to have attacked her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.47,0:07:12.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There was no such thing as a demon dog in the first place!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.01,0:07:13.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a psychological trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.22,0:07:18.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By using the myth of the cursed dog from\Nthe past and the flaming footprints...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.18,0:07:21.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit simply made it look as if a real demon dog existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.81,0:07:26.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They must've used fluorescent paint\Non the dog's body to make it glow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.90,0:07:28.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Fluorescent paint, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.57,0:07:29.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.90,0:07:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If something that doesn't normally light up is\Nglowing fiercely, you would think it was on fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.99,0:07:37.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, what about the flaming footprints?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.03,0:07:39.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no smell of oil, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.25,0:07:40.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.16,0:07:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They must've simply used a gas burner to light them one by one, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.63,0:07:47.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Kazuha?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.09,0:07:49.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It looks like we'll be here for a little while...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.30,0:07:52.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So go ahead to bed if you're feeling sleepy—
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.88,0:07:53.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,WHAT!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.14,0:07:56.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The demon dog showed up at the house!?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.52,0:08:00.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.10,0:08:03.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure that the dog was really on fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.02,0:08:04.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.52,0:08:06.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.02,0:08:09.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't anything like fluorescent paint.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.78,0:08:13.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although it's gone out now...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.11,0:08:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were even flaming footprints from each step that dog took.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.66,0:08:17.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.91,0:08:20.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are burn marks that match the ones above the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.20,0:08:24.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, where did that dog come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.92,0:08:26.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From over that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.88,0:08:31.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,These footprints are strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.72,0:08:38.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, judging by the interval between the footsteps,\Nthere should also be some prints around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.26,0:08:40.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this is the only place that had a wide gap.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.68,0:08:43.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention only this part of the ground was disturbed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.39,0:08:46.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that where you fell, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.82,0:08:55.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About the time when I fell...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.99,0:08:57.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I smelled some sort of strange odor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.66,0:09:00.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A strange odor?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.12,0:09:01.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What kind?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.16,0:09:03.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something like a rotten onion...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.58,0:09:05.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An odor that was harsh on the nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.87,0:09:06.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onion?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.54,0:09:09.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.84,0:09:14.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After we took refuge inside the house, we\Nimmediately went back outside to take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.38,0:09:16.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But they looked as if they were alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.51,0:09:19.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course that's the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.22,0:09:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dog attacked you, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.41,0:09:22.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.60,0:09:25.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not the demon dog, but the flaming footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.81,0:09:30.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They hopped around as if they were dancing,\Nand made crackling and popping noises.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.86,0:09:33.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} saw it too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.48,0:09:34.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.11,0:09:38.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was almost as if the footprints were possessed by spirits as well!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.37,0:09:41.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But to think you dared going back outside...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.99,0:09:43.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the demon dog supposed to be still around?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.29,0:09:47.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We knew that, but we were worried about Hachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.04,0:09:49.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We thought it might be eaten by the demon dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.71,0:09:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regarding the demon dog's infiltration route, I've found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.42,0:09:55.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was the back door.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.47,0:09:59.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was unlatched and left wide open...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.59,0:10:01.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there were dog prints as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.18,0:10:03.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In short...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.47,0:10:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit who brought the demon dog onto\Nthis property through the backdoor was...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.73,0:10:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone who was in this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.35,0:10:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's highly probable that it was among these four people!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.57,0:10:17.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since it'd be impossible for Satomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to\Nhave done it because she's bedridden.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.49,0:10:20.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Say, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}, you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.45,0:10:24.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said you came to the backyard in order to give Hachi its food...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.12,0:10:25.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who asked you to do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.66,0:10:27.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was Miyuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.06,0:10:28.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.79,0:10:31.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was because she said she was turned down by the other three.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.79,0:10:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it could be easily predicted that we'd\Nbe the ones taking the dog food out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.46,0:10:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, it is clear that someone has been raising\Nthe demon dog somewhere near this house.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.09,0:10:43.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.35,0:10:44.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it wasn't nearby...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.56,0:10:49.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit wouldn't have been able to set the dog on Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}'s\Nparty, who had suddenly been asked to do the feeding.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.94,0:10:52.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you happen to have any clues?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.61,0:10:55.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Such as hearing the barking of a dog in the forest or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.82,0:10:57.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now that you mention it...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.99,0:11:02.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, who was the second to pass away,\Ntold me about it and we went to inspect it once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.28,0:11:06.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said there was a strange cabin\Nwhere she could hear a dog barking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.49,0:11:10.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although we were too afraid to actually go inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.58,0:11:11.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What'd you say!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.00,0:11:12.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where was that!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.54,0:11:17.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it was near the marsh where Miwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.63,0:11:19.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lead us to there immediately!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.47,0:11:21.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Immediately?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.13,0:11:24.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we go immediately, we may be able to\Nfind out the trick behind the demon dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.55,0:11:25.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.43,0:11:31.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the culprit is among you, you wouldn't\Nhave had time to destroy the evidence yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.08,0:11:33.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.77,0:11:36.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am on duty tonight, so I need to get back to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.65,0:11:40.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Soon as we finish investigating the cabin, I'll give you a ride there!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.40,0:11:43.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention you may be afraid of going through\Nthat forest to get to the hospital by yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.20,0:11:45.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.62,0:11:48.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I merely followed Miwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.66,0:11:50.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As far as where that marsh is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.33,0:11:53.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's just to the marsh, I can show you the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.75,0:11:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I know my way around the forest...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.25,0:11:58.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it's not that far from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.46,0:12:15.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So this is the marsh...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.04,0:12:16.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.50,0:12:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is it true that the area around this marsh was on fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.63,0:12:20.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.74,0:12:24.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although we merely found burn marks here and there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.80,0:12:25.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.59,0:12:27.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where's the cabin you spoke of?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.35,0:12:28.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.60,0:12:32.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.58,0:12:34.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's that old cabin over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.29,0:12:38.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, let's advance into the demon dog's lair!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.34,0:12:42.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please watch your step.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.88,0:12:45.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This marsh seems to be bottomless.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.89,0:12:49.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're not coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.39,0:12:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no reason I should go, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.47,0:12:54.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll just wait inside the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.06,0:12:55.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That so?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.65,0:13:01.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.90,0:13:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the hell is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.99,0:13:06.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are black magic books all over the place!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.82,0:13:09.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even a magic circle is drawn here on the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.95,0:13:13.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no mistake that someone had been keeping a dog here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.75,0:13:15.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, who could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.96,0:13:19.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whoever it was placed a curse upon the dog here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.59,0:13:20.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moron!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.71,0:13:23.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you could kill someone using a curse,\Ndetectives would go out of business!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.55,0:13:27.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s art said the saw it...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.18,0:13:28.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like—we—said...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.97,0:13:31.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That was some sort of trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.81,0:13:36.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.79,0:13:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't struggle!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.79,0:13:57.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stay still!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.75,0:13:59.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is he all right!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.50,0:14:01.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Only suffered a slight burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.84,0:14:04.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.13,0:14:05.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What we saw just now...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.80,0:14:08.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was the demon dog, right...?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.14,0:14:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It showed up again!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.68,0:14:13.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying the demon dog showed up again!?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.97,0:14:14.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.97,0:14:17.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This makes for the third appearance tonight alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.56,0:14:19.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was that dog really on fire?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.56,0:14:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't that just some sort of trick?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.82,0:14:25.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, it crossed our minds, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.53,0:14:27.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No matter how you look at it...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.65,0:14:30.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's true that it was burning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.78,0:14:33.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Its body was engulfed in flickering flames to begin with...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.08,0:14:38.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And where that dog ran, flaming footprints would be left behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.66,0:14:43.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, Tomoaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s arm was on fire\Nwhen the demon dog attacked him...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.34,0:14:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And he suffered a burn!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.42,0:14:46.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.09,0:14:52.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I applied some first aid with the medical\Nsupplies I had in my bag, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.26,0:14:56.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had to call the hospital and get someone else to\Ntake my place as the on-duty doctor for tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.31,0:15:00.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, why did you get out of the car?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.31,0:15:04.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because I got scared while waiting all alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.11,0:15:10.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the problem is what had fallen next to\NTomoaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} after the demon dog attacked him...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.03,0:15:12.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This onion!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.37,0:15:15.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A round thing again?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.62,0:15:18.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.87,0:15:22.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of which, Kazuha{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, you mentioned it right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.12,0:15:24.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you fell as we were running from the demon dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.00,0:15:27.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That you smelled something like a rotten onion.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.67,0:15:33.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be that the demon dog and the onion are somehow related?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.68,0:15:34.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.85,0:15:38.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do the police have any leads regarding the culprit\Nthat's been pulling the strings behind the demon dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.27,0:15:46.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We did plan to call forensics in to investigate that\Nsuspicious cabin first thing in the morning, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.40,0:15:49.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We probably won't be able to arrest the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.74,0:15:50.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.78,0:15:52.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,BECAUSE!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.61,0:15:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our opponent is a black magic sorcerer who\Ncan place curses on dogs, remember!?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.78,0:16:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no way that normal mortals like we\Npolice officers could have the upper hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.00,0:16:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To tell the truth, I'd like to get away\Nfrom this place as soon as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.21,0:16:08.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Black magic"!?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.84,0:16:10.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were a lot of those in the cabin.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.13,0:16:13.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plenty of books like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.84,0:16:16.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm asking just in case, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.80,0:16:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When we encountered that demon dog...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.60,0:16:22.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,None of you had left this house, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.14,0:16:26.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was on the phone making arrangements\Nfor Saki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s funeral the whole time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.02,0:16:30.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was chatting on the computer with my surv game buddies.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.73,0:16:32.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Surv game?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.11,0:16:33.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You mean survival games?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.07,0:16:35.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.45,0:16:39.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm an instructor at a nearby campground.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.37,0:16:42.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Once a month, me and my buddies\Nwould do survival games together.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.12,0:16:46.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you're familiar with the forests around here as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.17,0:16:48.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorta...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.34,0:16:54.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, not as well as Miyuki who often\Ngathered wild plants with Mama Satomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.43,0:16:58.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And Satomi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was still—?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.76,0:16:59.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.97,0:17:01.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I believe she'd been sleeping in that room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.81,0:17:04.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By the way...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.35,0:17:06.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} and Hattori{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.15,0:17:09.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We haven't seen them for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.61,0:17:13.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're probably stupefied from the shock\Nand loafing around somewhere, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.19,0:17:16.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since they were convinced the demon dog was a trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.95,0:17:19.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But ended up witnessing it with their very own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.12,0:17:23.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.21,0:17:29.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're really at a loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.13,0:17:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just forget all that bad stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.25,0:17:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.71,0:17:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are bizarre things in this world that you can never\Ncomprehend, no matter how much you think about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.18,0:17:40.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Bizarre things that I can never comprehend?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.93,0:17:41.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.85,0:17:45.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What else, the demon dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.89,0:17:47.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You guys saw it too, right, Heiji?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.73,0:17:49.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That monster was on fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.61,0:17:53.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Dad said you guys even looked closely\Nat where the flaming foorprints were!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.69,0:17:57.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As far as the flaming footprints trick goes...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.03,0:18:01.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Based on the smell resembling a rotten onion\NKazuha noticed when she tripped...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.45,0:18:05.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And what Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r} saw immediately\Nafter the demon dog disappeared...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.41,0:18:09.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The flames making crackling noises and hopping\Naround —\hwe've pretty much figured out!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.38,0:18:14.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since the flaming footprints always\Nwent on for about twenty meters...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.88,0:18:18.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And some kind of drag marks were left on the ground, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.55,0:18:21.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, what we're really bothered by is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.97,0:18:23.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That fiery body.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.22,0:18:30.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did the culprit manage to set a fire on the dog that was\Nstrong enough to burn Tomoaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} when it pounced him?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.48,0:18:35.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If a cloth were put around a dog's body and set ablaze...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.19,0:18:38.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should've been a charred dog corpse somewhere in the area.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.82,0:18:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if the culprit had used water or a fire\Nextinguisher to put the flames out...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.12,0:18:44.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There should've been traces left behind, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.08,0:18:50.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they waited in a truck for the dog to come back,\Nand put out the fire on the loading bed...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.54,0:18:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There wouldn't be any evidence left, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.96,0:18:57.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were no tire tracks in the area, and\Nwe didn't hear the sound of an engine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.76,0:19:00.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's more, where did the dog disappear to?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.13,0:19:04.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it was on fire, when we rushed to Tomoaki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s aid...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.22,0:19:05.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We should have been able to see where it went.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.39,0:19:08.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the dog wasn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.89,0:19:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.23,0:19:12.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Almost as if it had been devoured by the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.15,0:19:14.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was devoured?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.57,0:19:16.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're saying it was eaten by the darkness?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.19,0:19:18.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you want to eat?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.45,0:19:21.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eat!?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.45,0:19:23.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean dinner...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.62,0:19:26.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to eat, shall I reheat it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.99,0:19:27.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll have some!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.91,0:19:28.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So hungry!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.33,0:19:30.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:31.54,0:19:32.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's something I want to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.71,0:19:36.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Does anything come to mind when I say balls or beads?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.13,0:19:38.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Balls?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.17,0:19:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit always leaves behind a\Nspherical object at the scene, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.09,0:19:46.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there some sort of link between this Inubushi home and spheres?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.81,0:19:50.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you say "sphere", what comes to mind is that...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.93,0:19:54.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My former surname was "Tamaki", and that's about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.40,0:19:58.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention my nickname back when I was a kid was Tama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.44,0:20:00.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tama{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.24,0:20:04.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But don't make me out to be the culprit just because of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.41,0:20:06.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Especially considering I'm not referred to by that nickname here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.58,0:20:09.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And do you know anything about the others' previous surnames?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.10,0:20:11.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.21,0:20:14.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since I was the last to come here and become an adopted child.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.88,0:20:19.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, you're quite a bit\Nyounger than the others, right Miyuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.55,0:20:20.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.63,0:20:26.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems I was conceived when my father,\NPresident Tsunechika, was in his mid fifties.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.09,0:20:31.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And my first name was supposed to be "Chikae",\Nwith a kanji taken from my father's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.02,0:20:33.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But my mother disliked it, so I got the name I'm using instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.81,0:20:36.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because my mother hated my father...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.27,0:20:38.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Saying she had been duped and dumped by a rich man.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.86,0:20:41.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, why did you come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.61,0:20:45.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you heard all those complaints from your\Nmother, shouldn't you be upset as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.49,0:20:49.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To tell the truth, I had no intention of coming here as well, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.04,0:20:53.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A little after my mother passed away due to illness...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.41,0:20:55.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I received a letter from Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.17,0:20:56.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Letter?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.08,0:20:59.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"My time is drawing near.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.38,0:21:01.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"If you would be so kind as to forgive me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.84,0:21:04.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to the Inubushi Manor and protect\Nthe princess for me," he wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.51,0:21:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I also heard all the other adopted\Nchildren received similar letters.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.26,0:21:11.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Regarding the "princess"...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.02,0:21:13.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.85,0:21:16.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wouldn't it mean Miyuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.52,0:21:18.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She has "princess" in her name, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.77,0:21:20.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moron.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.02,0:21:23.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would he write a letter to the princess\Nherself asking her to protect the princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.65,0:21:27.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't know who it was at first, either...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.41,0:21:31.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But once I came here, I immediately\Nrealized it meant Mother Satomi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.66,0:21:36.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because all the caretakers have been calling Mother a "princess".
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.50,0:21:37.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why is she the princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.63,0:21:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They said it was because Father had always called her that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.09,0:21:45.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although Mother would always jokingly tell them\Nto stop because she was embarrassed by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.55,0:21:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be because this manor is like a castle?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.93,0:21:52.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.31,0:21:55.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bet President Tsunechika felt like he was a feudal lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.81,0:21:58.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, about my name...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.06,0:22:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was supposed to be written as a single "kou"\Nkanji, and then to be read as Miyuki, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.19,0:22:02.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I followed Mother's recommendation...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.65,0:22:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And added the "princess" kanji.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.53,0:22:06.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I wasn't originally a princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.53,0:22:07.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You changed your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.32,0:22:09.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.24,0:22:14.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mother asked me to become a princess just like\Nher and live happily in this castle, that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.04,0:22:19.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaking of names...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.04,0:22:21.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There are interesting stories regarding how we were named.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.29,0:22:24.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your names, you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.05,0:22:28.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is likely to be among the remaining adopted children.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.26,0:22:35.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone who controlled a fiery demon dog and\Nassaulted the Inubushi family members one by one...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.22,0:22:38.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But who on earth is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.26,0:24:19.74,Signs,,0,0,0,,Prayer Beads
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.16,0:24:17.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next Conan's Hint
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.68,0:24:21.33,Signs,,0,0,0,,When something\Nlike a fiery dog\Nappears, you\Nshould go bite it!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.81,0:24:24.80,Signs,,0,0,0,,LOOK FORWARD TO THE NEXT EPISODE
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.35,0:24:22.37,Signs,,0,0,0,,What? Scary!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.40,0:24:23.54,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hot dog!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.70,0:24:24.39,Signs,,0,0,0,,Hold on...
